# NOTE: foundry-app/dist/ is intentionally NOT ignored. GitHub Pages
# serves from the built dist/ folder, so the pre-built bundle must be
# committed for the deploy to reflect source changes. Historically the
# `dist` line here blocked new build artifacts (e.g. new hash-named JS
# chunks) from being tracked while dist/index.html referenced them —
# producing a permanently broken deploy. Run `npm run build` before
# committing whenever src/ changes.
